NAME
orpgccz - Library routines used by ORPG to access clutter censor zone data.

SYNOPSIS

        #include <orpgccz.h>

        int ORPGCCZ_get_censor_zones( char *id, char **buf, int baseline )

        int ORPGCCZ_set_censor_zones( char *id, char *buf, int size, int baseline )

        int ORPGCCZ_baseline_to_default( char *id )

        int ORPGCCZ_default_to_baseline( char *id )

        int ORPGCCZ_get_edit_status( char *id )

        int ORPGCCZ_set_edit_lock( char *id )

        int ORPGCCZ_clear_edit_lock( char *id )

DESCRIPTION :

        The orpgccz library routines are used to access clutter censor zone
        data. 

	ORPGCCZ_get_censor_zones() reads the censor zone data identifed by id.
        The value for baseline should be either ORPGCCZ_DEFAULT or 
        ORPGCCZ_BASELINE, for default values or baseline values, respectively.
        On success, the size of the censor zone data is returned and censor
        zone data is copied to a malloc'd buffer pointed to by buf.  The caller
        is responsible for freeing associated with buf.   On error, a negative
        value is returned.  

	ORPGCCZ_set_censor_zones() writes the censor zone data identifed by id
        to the DEAU data base.  The value for baseline should be either 
        ORPGCCZ_DEFAULT or ORPGCCZ_BASELINE, for updating default values or 
        baseline values, respectively.  On success, the size of the censor zone 
        data writen is returned.  This value is likely larger than the size of 
        the data provided in buf since the data is stored encoded.  On error,
        a negative value is returned.  

	ORPGCCZ_baseline_to_default() and ORPGCCZ_default_to_baseline() 
        updates the default values in the DEAU database with the baseline values
        or the baseline values with the default values, respectivity.  The
        censor zone data updated is identified by either ORPGCCZ_LEGACY_ZONES
        or ORPGCCZ_ORDA_ZONES.  On success, 0 is returned.  On failure, a 
        negative error is returned.

        The ORPGCCZ_get_edit_status(), ORPGCCZ_set_edit_lock(), and 
        ORPGCCZ_clear_edit_lock() control multiple edits for clutter censor
        zone data. The routines allow users to check whether or not a process
        has placed a lock on particular clutter censor zone data identified
        by id. 

Options: None

See Also: deau(3), orpgedlock(3)

